    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-09-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-09-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="264" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d264">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hicks</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-09-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 1,
                                    1892</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 227.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received Mr. Neill’s dispatch No.
                            411, of the 3d ultimo, in regard to the claim of the Hydrographic
                            Commission of the Amazon.</p>
                <p>Now that the Peruvian Congress is again in session, the Department hopes
                            to secure intelligence that this admittedly just and long-standing claim
                            may be satisfactorily disposed of.</p>
                <p>You will accordingly continue your efforts to that end.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
